# Contributing to {{ project_name }}

Thanks for contributing!

## Workflow

1. Branch off `main` (it's protected — land changes via a PR).
2. {% if has_python %}Run `uv sync` to set up the dev environment, then install the hooks{% else %}Install the hooks{% endif %}: `uvx prek install`.
3. Make your change. The pre-commit hooks run the full quality gate — the same checks run in CI.
4. Commit with [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org) plus gitmoji,
   enforced by commitizen at commit-msg time.
5. Open a PR and make sure CI is green before requesting review.

## Running the quality gate

```bash
uvx prek run --all-files
```
